caption:
Step into confidence with Fabindia🌟@fabindiaofficial

From Monday morning meetings to casual Friday catch-ups, Fabindia has the perfect outfit for every day of the workweek. Whether it’s breezy kurtas or tailored tunics, these garments blend elegance with comfort, empowering every working woman.

Here’s how I style my week :

✨ Monday: Starting strong in a classic red kurta paired with Fabindia’s earthy-toned trousers, keeping it crisp and professional.
✨ Tuesday: Week meetings call for the effortless style of a chikankari kurta in soothing pastel tones
✨ Wednesday: A playful yet polished look with a block-printed tunic—perfect for presentations and team calls.
✨ Thursday: Elevating my energy with vibrant hues, I choose a handwoven, bright cotton kurta.
✨ Friday: My go-to? The cotton red dress! Paired with a bold, statement neckpiece, it’s my favorite piece to take me from work mode to weekend vibes with ease.

With Fabindia, you’re not just dressing for the day—you’re dressing to feel empowered, confident, and stylish every single day of the week. Because you deserve to look and feel your best every day!#AD

Fabindia recently hosted an exclusive event in Kolkata in the heritage Experience Centre on Loudon Street, bringing together fashion enthusiasts, social influencers, and eminent personalities for an afternoon of Pujo styling tips. 

The highlight of the event was an engaging panel discussion moderated by none other than Ms.Ushoshi Sengupta, Miss Universe India. The discussion centred around traditional Pujo attire, accessorising, and curating the perfect look for the much-awaited festival. From sari draping styles to curating indo-western outfits, the attendees were in for a treat.

The panel consisted of -

Ms.Ushoshi Sengupta, Miss Universe India
Dr. Rajeev Agarwal, Director Renew Healthcare
Ms. Esha Dutta, Director of Priya Cinemas 
Ms. Charvi Jain, Founder of Over a Cup of Tea 
TEDx speaker, Ms. Satabdi Bhattacharjee

Everyone also browsed through Fabindia’s latest Pujo collection, featuring an extensive range of handcrafted saris, kurtas, and accessories designed specifically for the festive season.

Flowers are everywhere, because the family 𝘗𝘰𝘰𝘬𝘢𝘭𝘢𝘮 is going to have new shapes, designs and flowers! Your ears fill with familiar songs only heard on Onam, impromptu dancing competitions are organised by family members, and happy confusion abounds!

Today is a big day, for everyone, including you are dressed in their festive best to head over to markets who open their doors for harvest sales!

Embrace the same joy at any Fabindia store near you, because we’re celebrating too!

Pujo days are more than a festival, it’s heartbeat of the year for all Bengalis wherever they are. The sound of 𝘥𝘩𝘢𝘬, the fragrance of fresh flowers for 𝘗𝘶𝘴𝘩𝘱𝘢𝘯𝘫𝘢𝘭𝘪, and the flicker of diyas during 𝘚𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘩𝘪 𝘗𝘶𝘫𝘰 stir something deep within us. The joy of celebrating together, the colours of the 𝘱𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘢𝘭𝘴, and the looking forward to devouring delicious bhog fill every corner of our hearts.

alt: Photo shared by Fabindia on August 02, 2024 tagging @fabindiahome. No hay ninguna descripción de la foto disponible..
caption:
Threading the historic needle

The process of bringing to you the best of Chikankari is elaborate and painstaking. Presenting to you a slight glimpse of it:

1. Craving out beautiful designs onto wooden blocks

2. Imprinting these blocks onto the fabric to create
 mesmerising patterns

3. Skilled artisans hand embroider onto these patterns

4. The fabric is then washed to remove impurities and unnecessary dyes.

5. Finishing touches are applied to make the final product.

And voila, it's available for you to shop at your nearest store!

Shop for this exquisite craft with kurtas, tops, shirts and more, at a store near you or online at fabindia.com. Download the app for instant access [link in bio].
